^{a})^{b}{\bmod {p}}}"></span>. Only Alice can determine the symmetric key =
and hence decrypt the message because only she has <i>a</i> (the private ke=
y). A pre-shared public key also prevents man-in-the-middle attacks.
</p><p>In practice, Diffie=E2=80=93Hellman is not used in this way, with <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_(cryptosystem)" class=3D"mw-redi=
rect" title=3D"RSA (cryptosystem)">RSA</a> being the dominant public key al=
gorithm. This is largely for historical and commercial reasons,<sup class=
=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<=
i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=
=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references t=
o reliable sources. (November 2015)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> =
namely that <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_(security_firm)" c=
lass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"RSA (security firm)">RSA Security</a> created=
 a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Certificate_authority" title=3D=
"Certificate authority">certificate authority</a> for key signing that beca=
me <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verisign" title=3D"Verisign">Ve=
risign</a>. Diffie=E2=80=93Hellman, as elaborated above, cannot directly be=
 used to sign certificates. However, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/ElGamal_signature_scheme" title=3D"ElGamal signature scheme">ElGamal=
</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_Signature_Algorit=
hm" title=3D"Digital Signature Algorithm">DSA</a> signature algorithms are =
mathematically related to it, as well as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/MQV" title=3D"MQV">MQV</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Station-to-Station_protocol" title=3D"Station-to-Station protocol">STS</a>=
 and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Key_Exchange" ti=
tle=3D"Internet Key Exchange">IKE</a> component of the <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPsec" title=3D"IPsec">IPsec</a> protocol suite for se=
curing <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Protocol" title=3D=
"Internet Protocol">Internet Protocol</a> communications.
</p>
